# Commit messages

Format: `type: message`. Keep messages short — no extended descriptions.

| Type       | Use for                                  |
| ---------- | ---------------------------------------- |
| `build`    | Build tooling, including Taskfiles       |
| `chore`    | Miscellaneous housekeeping               |
| `ci`       | CI configuration                         |
| `docs`     | Documentation and comments               |
| `feat`     | New or improved end-user behavior        |
| `fix`      | Bug fixes in end-user behavior           |
| `refactor` | Internal changes with no behavior change |
| `test`     | Test code                                |

If in doubt, what changed is more important than how it changed: test fixes are still `test`, build improvements are still `build`, and so on.

# Rewriting commits

It's okay to amend the last commit if it was made by you and the amendment increases clarity.
